Brawlers are unarmed close-quarters fighters descended from the pugilist tradition of laborers and dock workers.
They require no equipment or institutional backing to practice their art.
The tradition took its modern form in the harbor district fighting pits of Kowloon and Mafdet.
Combat role is sustained melee damage through raw physical toughness and tested techniques.
Training is demonstration-based, not theory-driven. Techniques that fail against resistant opponents are discarded.
Every technique has been validated under full-contact adversarial conditions.
Brawlers contrast with Monks, who begin from theoretical understanding rather than practice.
Brawler intensity tends to degrade over extended fights, a weakness the Monk synthesis corrects.
The Martial Artist class synthesizes Brawler practical combat with Monk interior discipline.
